  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "# Feature Issue\r\n\r\nPrevent one of the most common mistakes in ERC20 newbies, sending (burning) their tokens while trying to paste the ERC20 token in the wallet configuration.\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I don't want to burn my tokens, and I expect the wallet software to forbid me to do such a mistake.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nThis issue is part of the #11136 effort. \r\n\r\nWhile the warning should prevent most errors, there is no reason for accepting a user to send their tokens to the token contract address itself. \r\n\r\nDifferent from the general warning, this would be an error message which would not allow the user to proceed. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n\r\nImpossible to send an ERC20 to the token contract itself.\r\n",
